casebody.data:
SMITH v. WARDEN OF MARYLAND HOUSE OF CORRECTION [H. C. No. 97,

September Term, 1957.]

Decided April 25, 1958.

Before Bruñe, C. J., and Henderson, Hammond, Prescott and Horney, Jj.

*648Per Curiam.

In this application for leave to appeal, the petitioner raises no questions reviewable in a habeas corpus proceeding, and the application is denied for the reasons stated in the opinion of the trial court.
